Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5.0.35), bzip2, dpatch
Standards-Version: 3.7.2

Package: ivtv-utils
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${perl:Depends}, libconfig-inifiles-perl, libvideo-ivtv-perl, unzip
Recommends: perl-tk, devscripts, fakeroot
Description: utilities for use with the ivtv kernel driver
 The primary goal of the IvyTV Project is to create a kernel driver
 for the iTVC15 family of MPEG codecs. The iTVC15 family includes the
 iTVC15 (CX24315) and iTVC16 (CX24316). These chips are commonly found
 on Hauppauge's WinTV PVR-250 and PVR-350 TV capture cards.
 .
 This package contains the 0.7 branch of the IVTV utilities.

Package: ivtv-source
Architecture: all
Depends: module-assistant, bzip2, debhelper (>= 5.0.35), dpatch
Description: source for ivtv drivers (0.7 branch)
 The primary goal of the IvyTV Project is to create a kernel driver
 for the iTVC15 familiy of MPEG codecs. The iTVC15 family includes the
 iTVC15 (CX24315) and iTVC16 (CX24316). These chips are commonly found
 on Hauppauge's WinTV PVR-250 and PVR-350 TV capture cards.
 .
 This package contains the module source for the 0.7 branch of the
 IVTV driver. The kernel driver can be built from it using
 module-assistant or make-kpkg. This version of the driver only works
 with kernel 2.6.17

